claims:
29. A method comprising:
sintering a plurality of nanocrystalline particulates to form a nanocrystalline alloy;
wherein
at least some of the nanocrystalline particulates comprise a non-equilibrium phase comprising a first metal material and a second metal material;
the first metal material is soluble in the second metal material; and
the nanocrystalline alloy has a relative density of at least about 90%.
